uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.swing

Class ReFetchTargetVisitor<T,K>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.swing.ReFetchTargetVisitor<T,K>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TransitionFactoryVisitor<T,T,K>

    public class ReFetchTargetVisitor<T,K>
extends java.lang.Object
implements TransitionFactoryVisitor<T,T,K>
    A TransitionFactoryVisitor that performs a clean re-fetch of the target. This is to allow the target to be re-fetched within a database transaction. Note that this can (and usually does) destroy the original copy of the target.
